The President and Administration officials, including Health and Human Services Secretary Sebelius, held a videoconference with directors of State-based health insurance Marketplaces. The President thanked those working on the frontlines and heard about the progress made in setting up the Marketplaces. The President reiterated the Administration's support and encouraged participants to share best practices for outreach and enrollment efforts. The President recognized the diligence, creativity, and commitment of those working in the States to set up the Marketplaces. Under the Affordable Care Act, health insurance Marketplaces will open on October 1st, where Americans can shop for quality, affordable coverage. Tax credits will be available to help make health insurance more affordable. Plans offered in the Marketplace will include new consumer protections such as no discrimination based on pre-existing conditions or gender, no annual or lifetime limits on coverage, a cap on out-of-pocket costs, and a requirement that insurance plans cover essential services. Americans are encouraged to visit HealthCare.gov for more information.